image.altText: A French player runs away with arms out in celebration as the ball lies in the back of the net.

items.synopsis: France get the vital opener against Brazil in Brisbane, after Sweden sweeps aside the challenge of Italy in Wellington. Follow live.

title.children: French take the lead against Brazil after Sweden sweep Italy aside in Wellington

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: It's Wendie Renard, the captain, making the run from a corner and heading past the keeper. Inspirational from the irrepresible centre-back, who is the 7th highest scorer for France. Can't emphasise enough how good that run was, to get on the end of that, she almost ran in a semi-circle so smash it into the ground and into the net.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 84' GOAAAAAAAAAAL FRANCE!! Is that the winner?

children.content: It's Wendie Renard, the captain, making the run from a corner and heading past the keeper.
Inspirational from the irrepresible centre-back, who is the 7th highest scorer for France.
Can't emphasise enough how good that run was, to get on the end of that, she almost ran in a semi-circle so smash it into the ground and into the net.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A long, patient build up, and Debinha gets the finish! The Brazilians had worked it from right to left, with Debinha making a darting run that was timed perfectly, her first touch was perfect too. Just what this match needed.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 58' GOAAAAAAAL Brazil!!

children.content: A long, patient build up, and Debinha gets the finish!
The Brazilians had worked it from right to left, with Debinha making a darting run that was timed perfectly, her first touch was perfect too.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Le Sommer's header the difference in a fantastic first half. Probably the highest standard of football we've seen at the tournament, along with USA-Netherlands the other day. Wonderful to watch. France have controlled the game for periods and largely shut down Brazil's passing game, but there are still flashes from the South Americans that make you think they could score at any time. Debinha looks the most likely to create a spark.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: France 1 - 0 Brazil

children.content: Le Sommer's header the difference in a fantastic first half.
Probably the highest standard of football we've seen at the tournament, along with USA-Netherlands the other day.

Wonderful to watch. France have controlled the game for periods and largely shut down Brazil's passing game, but there are still flashes from the South Americans that make you think they could score at any time. Debinha looks the most likely to create a spark.
